  "sections": {
    "Background": {
      "text": "Occurs via forceful contraction of quadriceps muscle or falling on flexed knee\nTypically occur 2cm from insertion on patella",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "Sudden \"pop\" or tearing\nDiffuse swelling\nDefect may be palpable below the patella\nPartial tears lead to difficulty extending the knee\nComplete tears lead to absent straight leg raise while supine or extension of the knee again",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
